Jeff Wicks, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; Police in northern KwaZulu-Natal on Monday arrested a hitchhiker accused of murdering an Eshowe school principal last week.Police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said the 23-year-old man was arrested during an operation by Eshowe detectives who were charged with investigating the killing."It is alleged that the 44-year-old victim, Busisiwe Nzuza, offered a lift to a hitchhiker from Empangeni towards Eshowe."While on the way, near Nkwalini, the hitchhiker allegedly produced a firearm and demanded the vehicle from the principal. He allegedly shot the victim [in] the head and [she] died instantly," Mbhele added.The gunman then fled the scene on foot.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.